The issues is not only that the damaged fuel rods (about 10% of the full core) may melt from residual decay heat (as bad as that may be), but that an unplanned critical array may be created in this cleaning tank, - a chain reaction. This cleaning tank is not a reactor vessel. As poor in safety features the VVER-440 reactor may be, the safety features of this cleaning tank appear to be zero. The fuel assemblies may be unmovable due to the risk of the damaged rods.<br>
<br>
I would asume that they are flooding the tank with borated water.<br>
<br>
I hope that the IAEA is sending experts.<br>
